{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "a3784989-bfcf-4062-9421-256331202883",
    "name": "Universal Store APIs",
    "description": "Contract and integration tests for the **Catalog**, **Inventory**, and **PLP BFF** services in the Universal Store take-home assessment.\n\n## Purpose\n\nThis collection verifies that all services:\n\n- Return correct HTTP status codes\n    \n- Match expected response shapes\n    \n- Serve seeded test data correctly\n    \n- Honor the cross-service contract: every inventory SKU must exist in the catalog\n    \n- The BFF merges catalog + inventory and returns only in-stock products\n    \n\nIt is intended for **interactive debugging in Postman** and **automated runs via Newman** (`tests/postman/`).\n\n## Prerequisites\n\n- **Catalog service** running at `{{catalogUrl}}` (default: `http://localhost:3000`)\n    \n- **Inventory service** running at `{{inventoryUrl}}` (default: `http://localhost:4000`)\n    \n- **PLP BFF** running at `{{bffUrl}}` (default: `http://localhost:5000`)\n    \n- Databases seeded (via `docker compose up` or manual seed scripts)\n    \n\nSelect the **Local** environment before running requests.\n\n## Collection structure\n\n### Catalog\n\n| Request | Validates |\n| --- | --- |\n| `GET /catalog` | 200, array of ≥4 items with `sku`, `title`, `price`, `image`; stores SKUs in `catalogSkus` |\n| `GET /catalog/:sku` (exists) | 200, returns Pen (`111111`) |\n| `GET /catalog/:sku` (404) | 404 for unknown SKU |\n\n### Inventory\n\n| Request | Validates |\n| --- | --- |\n| `GET /inventory` | 200, array of ≥4 items with `sku` and `quantity`; SKU `444444` has quantity `0` |\n| `GET /inventory/:sku` (exists) | 200, returns item; SKU `111111` has quantity `3` |\n| `GET /inventory/:sku` (404) | 404 for unknown SKU |\n\n### PLP BFF\n\n| Request | Validates |\n| --- | --- |\n| `GET /products/in-stock` | 200, merged in-stock products with `sku`, `title`, `price`, `image`, `quantity`; excludes SKU `444444` |\n\n### Contract\n\n| Request | Validates |\n| --- | --- |\n| Every inventory SKU exists in catalog | Each inventory SKU is present in `catalogSkus` (set by `GET /catalog`) |\n\n## Run order\n\nRun **Catalog → Inventory → PLP BFF → Contract** when using Collection Runner. The Contract test depends on `catalogSkus`, which is set by the first Catalog request.\n\n## Running via Newman\n\n\\`\\`\\`bash  \ncd tests/postman  \nnpm run test:postman",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json",
