      "description": "Tests for the **Inventory** microservice (`{{inventoryUrl}}`, port 4000).\n\nReturns stock levels keyed by `sku` and `quantity`.\n\n| Request | Validates |\n| --- | --- |\n| `GET /inventory` | 200, array of ≥4 items; SKU `444444` has quantity `0` |\n| `GET /inventory/:sku` (exists) | 200, returns item; SKU `111111` has quantity `3` |\n| `GET /inventory/:sku` (404) | 404 for unknown SKU |"
    },
    {
      "name": "PLP BFF",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "GET /products/in-stock",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('status is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('returns an array', () => pm.expect(body).to.be.an('array'));",
                  "pm.test('returns 3 in-stock products', () => pm.expect(body.length).to.eql(3));",
                  "pm.test('items have required fields', () => {",
                  "  body.forEach(item => {",
                  "    pm.expect(item).to.have.property('sku');",
                  "    pm.expect(item).to.have.property('title');",
                  "    pm.expect(item).to.have.property('price');",
                  "    pm.expect(item).to.have.property('image');",
                  "    pm.expect(item).to.have.property('quantity');",
                  "  });",
                  "});",
                  "const skus = body.map(i => i.sku);",
                  "pm.test('includes in-stock SKUs', () => {",
                  "  pm.expect(skus).to.include('111111');",
                  "  pm.expect(skus).to.include('222222');",
                  "  pm.expect(skus).to.include('333333');",
                  "});",
                  "pm.test('excludes out-of-stock SKU 444444', () => pm.expect(skus).to.not.include('444444'));",
                  "const pen = body.find(i => i.sku === '111111');",
                  "pm.test('Pen has merged catalog + inventory data', () => {",
                  "  pm.expect(pen.title).to.eql('Pen');",
                  "  pm.expect(pen.quantity).to.eql(3);",
                  "  pm.expect(pen.price).to.eql(3);",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{bffUrl}}/products/in-stock",
              "host": [
                "{{bffUrl}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "products",
                "in-stock"
              ]
            }
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ],
      "description": "Tests for the **PLP BFF** (`{{bffUrl}}`, port 5000).\n\nMerges catalog and inventory data and returns only products with quantity > 0.\n\n| Request | Validates |\n| --- | --- |\n| `GET /products/in-stock` | 200, 3 merged items; excludes SKU `444444` (Marker) |"
    },
    {
      "name": "Contract",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Every inventory SKU exists in catalog",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "const inventory = pm.response.json();",
                  "const catalogSkus = JSON.parse(pm.collectionVariables.get('catalogSkus'));",
                  "inventory.forEach(item => {",
                  "  pm.test(`inventory sku ${item.sku} exists in catalog`, () => {",
                  "    pm.expect(catalogSkus).to.include(item.sku);",
                  "  });",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{inventoryUrl}}/inventory",
              "host": [
                "{{inventoryUrl}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "inventory"
              ]
            }
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ],
      "description": "Cross-service contract tests between Catalog and Inventory.\n\nThe **PLP BFF** aggregates data from both services to show in-stock products. These tests verify the underlying data contract the BFF depends on: every inventory SKU must exist in the catalog.\n\n| Request | Validates |\n| --- | --- |\n| Every inventory SKU exists in catalog | Each inventory SKU is in `catalogSkus` (set by Catalog `GET /catalog`) |\n\n**Must run after the Catalog folder** so `catalogSkus` is populated."
    }
